    teaching: "One week into activation. Pause here.\n\nThis week you worked directly with the Ajna centre. You did the central activation meditation. You cleared energy blocking the channel. You began serious dream work. You moved through the full chakra column. This is significant work.\n\nThe body and psyche need time to integrate what has been stirred and opened. Integration is not laziness. It is half of the transformation. The insights that arise during periods of rest are often the most important.\n\nSome of you will have had experiences this week that felt uncomfortable, disorienting, or emotionally challenging. Old grief surfacing. Unexpected anger. Dreams that disturbed rather than comforted. Moments of confusion about who you are and what you want.\n\nThis is not a sign that something has gone wrong. This is the clearing in action. When you open the channel, everything sitting in the channel comes through on its way out. The uncomfortable experiences are part of the healing, not evidence against it.\n\nIf the process feels genuinely overwhelming, reach out. Message David on WhatsApp. You do not need to navigate this alone. The ancient initiates had guides. You do too.\n\nToday is yours. There is no formal practice beyond your morning ritual. The day itself is the practice.",
    practice: "Part 1 \u2014 Journal Review (10 minutes):\nRead back through your journal entries from Days 15\u201320. Don\u2019t analyse \u2014 simply read. Notice what stands out now that didn\u2019t when you wrote it. Notice patterns, recurring symbols, recurring feelings.\n\nPart 2 \u2014 The Week 3 Integration Questions:\nSit with these questions. Take your time with each.\n\n\u2022 What has genuinely shifted in how I perceive the world since beginning this cohort?\n\u2022 What has my dream life been showing me this week? Is there a consistent theme?\n\u2022 Where in my body do I feel most open? Where do I still feel resistance?\n\u2022 What truth has the inner eye shown me that my thinking mind has been resistant to accepting?\n\u2022 What am I being called to release in order to open more fully?\n\u2022 What am I being called toward?\n\nPart 3 \u2014 Rest:\nTake a nap, walk in nature, or sit in silence for as long as feels right. Today is about receiving, not doing.",
